      "Lohri is one of the most socially vibrant winter festivals in North India, especially in Punjab and neighboring regions. It is celebrated on a cold evening around a community bonfire, with songs, dance, sweets, and shared warmth. The outer form is simple, but the emotional value is deep: welcome seasonal transition together, not alone.",
