      "## Message Framework Students Can Use",
      "Use a three-line structure. Line 1: thank-you statement. Line 2: specific impact example. Line 3: future-oriented respect line. This format works for handwritten cards, WhatsApp notes, speech scripts, and school boards.",
      "If your relationship is formal, keep the tone respectful and concise. If your mentor relationship is close, a warmer conversational tone works well.",
      "## School And Classroom Celebration Ideas",
      "Good Teachers Day programs do not need large budgets. Tribute walls, student storytelling segments, short gratitude circles, and classroom memory boards create strong emotional value at low cost. Handwritten notes still outperform expensive gifts for sincerity.",
      "Schools can also include student-led sessions where each class shares one learning value they will carry forward. This turns appreciation into action.",
      "## For Parents And Alumni",
      "Parents can involve children by helping them identify one teacher behavior they admire. Alumni can send brief impact updates to former teachers. A simple 'your advice still guides me' message can be deeply meaningful years later.",
      "These small gestures strengthen educational culture and remind teachers that their influence continues beyond the classroom period.",
      "## Final Takeaway",
      "Teachers Day works best when appreciation is honest, specific, and respectful. You do not need long poetry. You need one real reason and a clear thank-you.",
